    {
      "id": "b5e909e4a6094eea280c04dff6168444b05e0896",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 242,
        "name": "Liu Xuezhao",
        "email": "xuezhao.liu@emc.com",
        "username": "XuezhaoLiu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-05-29 03:01:09.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi,\n\nThere is still one BKL call in libcfs/libcfs/linux/linux-prim.c's cfs_daemonize.\n\nIt seems to me that the lock_kernel/unlock_kernel in cfs_daemonize totally not needed?\nAnd there are some other obsolete HAVE_UNLOCKED_IOCTL in code.\n\nWill you remove the above in your patch? Or I will remove them in libcfs cleanup patch.\n\nThanks!",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "0537c407bd48bf11452823bb0ffb4b3340e2e9d7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 101,
        "name": "Lai Siyao",
        "email": "lai.siyao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "laisiyao"
      },
      "date": "2012-05-29 03:19:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nXuezhao, you're right, I missed the code in libcfs. You may create a patch under LU-506 and cleanup the remaining code.\nIt looks fine to me to remove lock_kernel() from cfs_daemonize().",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "f535b9ac25ac370639a954fe9a932bb48a535a64",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 242,
        "name": "Liu Xuezhao",
        "email": "xuezhao.liu@emc.com",
        "username": "XuezhaoLiu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-05-29 03:28:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOK, then I will format a small patch and submit it to LU-506.\nThanks.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
